<title type="html"><![CDATA[Attributes with 32x32 Metatiles]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6309&amp;p=60244#p60244"><![CDATA[
I was thinking of using a method down the road that went like this:<br /><br />Since under most circumstances there can only be 4 palettes, as long as you have less then 64 meta-tiles total you can steal 2 bits from each byte to assign the palette.<br /><br />so if i had "%01000001", the first 2 bits are the attribute data (palette 2), the next 6 bits assign the tile as meta-tile number 1. Use a bitmask to split the byte.<br /><br />As long as you have less then 64 meta-tiles, your attributes are "free" (minus the code to split them).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3869">ProgrammingAce</a> — Thu Apr 22, 2010 2:31 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
